spanGrp.span: a man was bringing down fruits; he was on a tree,
pekaga dul mansana wö bötsö dul kaljula nã
all concentrated and did not see the child coming on a bike.
í wö da jirö bötsö (_) ka í *të sunẽ yaba dajũ bisikleta inga
He realized that the load was in a basket.
Je wöjanã'-wã í deli ska kalu jaba nã
He turned to see the man; the man was not looking,
Ñerö í wöká pekaga sũã' Ka pe ku/ pekaga kuna í sũã' (_)
he took them, put them into the basket until he could fill it up, and put them on the bike to carry that load.
(_) Je jiátei-te (_) beteũ (_) jaba nã mansana wö kalu kö shi jiá-wã-ite í bisikleta í deli sigö-glö nã
Then he left and was going far away on his bike,
Jebi í mẽnẽu-mĩ tara dömĩ komĩ' ñala wa Jie shkö-gate í bisikleta inga
when he saw a girl coming towards him on a bike.
jeska í të (extra) pebusi sũã'-ite dajũ-nẽ jigwetatenẽ bisikleta inga
They went on and turned to stare at the girl,
Ñerö jie jie sige-nã-gate-nẽ í wöká-wã jerre je pebusi sũã'
and then his bike crashed against a fucking stone.
Ta í bisikleta kenã' chi jak mẽ
Everything broke and fell to the ground;
Ñerö í bötsanã'u-mĩ Jekea í deli kenã'sã' klabe
his knee crashed on the ground.
Ta í kichewö kenã' jishugö mẽ
He sat down to clean it.
He had not seen that there were three men around;
Ka í *të sunẽ ke jeska mãñã-l jeyiwa kajalali
these helped him pick up the stuff.
Je të í kimã' í kögá të í kimã'-nẽ í deli wö pakköchö-wã-nẽ í jaba nã
He then hurried on his bike.
Ñerö jie… jie sigenã' junã' bisikleta inga
he/they found his hat on the ground.
je të í sombrero kwã' jiski inga
One of the others came to give it to him;
Ñerö (_) í siga-wa e-gla bötö-nẽ jie ĩã í juã'
there he gave that one three apples and moved on on his bike.
Ñerö jie të jeska mãñã-l mansana wö kagumã' ĩã Ñerö jie sige-nã' bisikleta inga í
Then the man bringing down fruits came down and saw that there was a basket missing;
tara *mẽ mãĩ pekaga kalu (m) kalu je mansana wö bötsö je jẽk jiá-te í deu-nẽ jiski inga ra í sũã'-ite-ra ka e-gla jaba jue-nã
but I had a full basket, where is it?”’
“pero ñera yís të (m) e-gla jaba kalu sh shshsh shi ¿mãga í de nã”
